            We did what was required but I feel we missed out on a big tally. Zagreb looked very much there for the taking and it's not an overstatement to say we could've had 6 or 7. I understand why Wenger brought the 3 players he did on but I wanted to see how Reine-Adelaide faired against proper opposition. We already know he's great in the under ages, I think Arsene missed a trick not playing him today. I'm confident we can beat Olympiakos by 2 or more goals with our first XI fit. Giroud didn't do much today but I think we'll play Walcott in Greece anyway, providing he is fit obviously, because of his pace.
